ree days down a dirt road, carrying everything they owned. John would recall that journey in great detail his entire life. As a young man, before finishing his high school education, he left home to fight in the Korean War so that he could support his mother. As a young father of five, he took every job imaginable to support his family, including unloading banana boats and working to build the Alaskan pipeline. He tragically saw two of his children die before he reached the age of sixty. He had a hard life and was used to bad news.\",\"index\":152,\"type\":\"markdown\",\"summarizable\":true},{\"content\":\"John Wiley did not call me for casual reasons. If he called, it was serious, possibly even deadly serious.\",\"index\":153,\"type\":\"markdown\",\"summarizable\":true},{\"hierarchy\":[{\"content\":\"Ben: “Hello.”\",\"index\":154,\"type\":\"markdown\",\"summarizable\":true},{\"content\":\"John: “Ben, the office said not to bother you, but I just want to let you know that Felicia stopped breathing, but she is not going to die.”\",\"index\":155,\"type\":\"markdown\",\"summarizable\":true},{\"content\":\"Ben: “Not going to die? What?!?! What happened?”\",\"index\":156,\"type\":\"markdown\",\"summarizable\":true},{\"content\":\"I could not believe it. I had been so focused on work that I had lost focus of the only thing that really mattered to me. Once again, I neglected to worry about the one thing that I should have worried about.\",\"index\":157,\"type\":\"markdown\",\"summarizable\":true},{\"content\":\"Ben: “What happened?”\",\"index\":158,\"type\":\"markdown\",\"summarizable\":true},{\"content\":\"John: “They gave her some medicine and she had an allergic reaction and she stopped breathing, but she’s okay now.”\",\"index\":159,\"type\":\"markdown\",\"summarizable\":true},{\"content\":\"Ben: “When?”\",\"index\":160,\"type\":\"markdown\",\"summarizable\":true},{\"content\":\"John: “Yesterday.”\",\"index\":161,\"type\":\"markdown\",\"summarizable\":true},{\"content\